# TypeScript & Code Quality

## Always verify types before completing work

- Use `read_lints` tool after making edits to check for TypeScript errors
- Never commit code with TypeScript errors - fix type mismatches immediately
- Prefer proper TypeScript types over `any` or `unknown` when possible

## Type conversion patterns

When converting between string/number types, use explicit conversions:
- `Number(id)` or `parseInt(id, 10)` for string to number
- `String(value)` for number to string
- Verify type compatibility when passing data between components/stores

## API response types

- Ensure API response types match store/component types
- Convert string IDs to numbers when needed (see `@frontend/components/SearchImageByAI.vue:50` for example)
- Reference `@frontend/J/useArtistsStore.ts` for Artist type definition

## Before claiming work is complete

1. Run `read_lints` on modified files
2. Fix all TypeScript compilation errors
3. Verify type compatibility in function parameters and return values
4. Check for type mismatches when passing data between components/stores
